g.text: Estación de Recepción Migratoria (ERM)San Vicente (Darién) San Vincente, Panamá
Migrants board a government bus costing $40 at San Vincente, Panamá going to Chirqui in northern Panamá.
The average migrant has spent $865 by the time they have made it past the Panamá Canal.
Each arrow represents the accumulated cost a migrant has made. The average accumulated cost once migrants reach Chiriqui, Panamá is $891 and they still have many kilometers left in their journey.
Bajo Chiquito is the first stopafter making the difficult walkthrough the Darién Jungle. Many migrants need food andwater.
